description:
The investment seeks a high level of income; capital appreciation is a secondary objective.
 The fund invests primarily in high yield, high risk debt securities. Under normal circumstances, it invests at least 80% of its assets in high yield securities. For purposes of this policy, "assets" means net assets plus the amount of borrowings for investment purposes. The fund may invest up to 100% of its total assets in below investment grade or unrated securities. The adviser uses a multi-factor security selection process that uses factors that the adviser believes reflect liquidity and issuer quality.
